data.description: This inviting traditional-style home is nestled on a quiet street in Moss Grove Plantation. The HVAC was newly installed in 2022. You may enjoy energy savings from the solar panels (to be paid off by the seller at closing). The attached two-car garage gives you plenty of space for parking and storage. As you enter, you're greeted by laminate floors, fresh paint, smooth tall ceilings, and a spacious open floor plan with a great flow for entertaining and everyday living. The open kitchen boasts recessed lighting, granite countertops, a stylish subway tile backsplash, ample cabinet and counter space, a pantry for additional storage, a large breakfast bar, and a breakfast/casual dining area overlooking the backyard.Upstairs, you'll find new carpet throughout. The spacious master bedroom features a walk-in closet and a private en suite bathroom with ceramic tile flooring, a dual vanity, a garden tub, and a separate shower. The rest of the bedrooms are also spacious in size. The upstairs loft area would make an excellent game room, entertainment room, children's play area, or home office. The patio and privacy-fenced backyard will be perfect for grilling out, entertaining, or watching the kids and/or pets play. You'll appreciate neighborhood amenities, including a community pool, a clubhouse, a covered picnic pavilion, a playground, and a pond with a kayak launch. Conveniently located near shopping and dining. Come see your new home, today!
